&lt;p&gt;Bridgeway is seeking a QA Engineer to work in a fast-paced, results driven environment, collaborating with other engineers and analysts. The QA Engineer is responsible for ensuring the quality, reliability, and performance of software products through automated and manual testing practices. Quality Assurance Engineers are integral to the SDLC, leveraging automation frameworks, tooling, and testing strategies to detect defects early, validate requirements, and prevent regressions. This role focuses on building scalable, repeatable, and maintainable automated test solutions that support CI/CD. Quality Assurance Engineers partner closely with software engineers, quality analysts, product owners, business analysts, scrum masters, and platform teams to ensure quality is embedded throughout the development process—improving user experience while reducing risk, rework, and post-release defects. We are seeking a highly motivated individual who thrives in a highly productive team centric environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a remote position with preference given to East Coast candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze and understand business, product, infrastructure, and technical requirements to ensure comprehensive test coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional stakeholders to clarify requirements, identify risks, and ensure acceptance criteria are testable and automatable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define testing strategies and approaches that align with DevOps and CI/CD practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify testing scope, objectives, resources, timelines, and deliverables for automated and manual testing efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop, and maintain well-structured, reusable, and maintainable automated test cases and frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and manage automated test scripts and test suites within Azure DevOps (ADO) or similar platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute and maintain automated and manual tests, including functional, regression, performance, usability, and security testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiate and monitor automated test runs, analyze results, and validate test coverage for assigned scrum teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, document, prioritize, and track defects and inconsistencies, partnering closely with developers to troubleshoot issues and validate fixes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a strong understanding of user story sizing, test planning, and test coverage within Agile and Scrum workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear and detailed documentation of test plans, test cases, automation frameworks, and regression testing results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and communicate test results, regression reports, and quality metrics to technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively contribute to the automation roadmap by identifying opportunities to increase automation coverage and improve testing efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend and implement process, tooling, and framework improvements to enhance the effectiveness, scalability, and reliability of the QA practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current with industry trends, tools, and best practices in test automation, quality engineering, and secure software development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage generative AI tools such as Claude and Copilot to streamline workflows, enhance productivity, improve solution quality, and accelerate delivery of business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of professional software quality assurance experience, including 2+ years in test automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with test automation tools and frameworks (e.g., TestComplete, Playwright)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid programming skills in Java, P

&lt;p&gt;Bridgeway is seeking a Senior Platform Engineer to architect, design, develop, and maintain the Bridgeway platform that powers software development and deployment. This role focuses on building robust, scalable, and efficient platforms that enable teams to develop, test, and deploy applications seamlessly. As a Platform Engineer, you will combine software engineering, systems architecture, and operations to ensure Bridgeway’s cloud infrastructure platform meets the needs of multiple applications and services. You will also help drive an organizational mindset rooted in DevOps, DevSecOps, Site Reliability Engineering (SRE), and modern Cloud Engineering practices. Successful candidates are resourceful, inventive, and forward-thinking—able to solve complex challenges creatively, integrate diverse systems, and progressively shape the future of our platform. At the senior level, we seek engineers who bring both depth and breadth of expertise, leveraging cross-disciplinary mastery to collaborate effectively and drive innovative, holistic solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a remote position with preference given to East Coast candidates.   &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Iteratively design and develop scalable, resilient, and efficient platform solutions using cloud services and modern software design frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create modular, reusable infrastructure using Terraform and related tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner interdepartmentally and cross-functionally to strengthen DevOps practices through automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect,&amp;nbsp;develop, and maintain CI/CD pipelines for platform functions and customer needs at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver solutions based on event-driven, object-oriented, and functional design patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the design and implementation of monitoring and logging solutions to ensure reliability and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the definition and maintenance of a lifecycle process for platform systems to ensure updates, patches, and security compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply deep expertise in platform engineering while leveraging cross-disciplinary knowledge to drive effective collaboration across development, operations, and security teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve cloud infrastructure issues quickly, analyze performance, and implement improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze system performance and implement optimizations to improve speed, efficiency, and resource&amp;nbsp;utilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipate and plan infrastructure scaling to meet the growing needs of the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply a security-first approach, ensuring SOC, SOC2, HIPAA, NIST, and regulatory requirements are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and manage IAM, firewalls, and SIEM solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate diverse and non-traditional systems to deliver practical, forward-thinking outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate challenges creatively and find effective solutions when conventional approaches fall short&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead assigned projects, driving cross-team collaboration, execution&amp;nbsp;delivery, and accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write clean, efficient, and well-documented code while following best practices and established development standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take part&amp;nbsp;in the on-call rotation to ensure the reliability and availability of platform services.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage generative AI tools such as Claude and Copilot to streamline workflows, enhance productivity, improve solution quality, and accelerate delivery of business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of platform, cloud, or SRE engineering

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Senior Systems Analyst to lead complex data conversion efforts for our customers. In this role, you’ll lead the end-to-end data conversion lifecycle, working directly with customers to analyze, map, transform, validate, and load data from their legacy systems into Bridgeway’s software platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This hands-on, customer-facing role requires strong cross-functional collaboration, real-time problem solving, data mapping and transformation expertise, and the ability to drive migrations through a successful go-live.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead full-cycle data conversions for multiple large-scale projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with customers and internal teams to analyze and profile legacy data, document source-to-target mapping requirements, and apply technical skills and AI-assisted development to transform and load data into Bridgeway’s platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Business Analysts and other Professional Services teams to understand business requirements, provide data analyses to assist with the configuration of our software, and accurately map data to meet customer needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze, transform and validate large, complex datasets using advanced SQL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and execute ETL/ELT processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop data mapping logic, transformation rules, and validation strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and resolve data quality issues through profiling, cleansing, and root cause analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with multiple file formats (CSV, Excel, Fixed Width) to support data exchange&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute cutover activities, including go-live coordination and validation sign-off&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal teams to troubleshoot issues and ensure accurate data delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior team members and contribute to improving migration processes and standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage generative AI tools such as Claude and Copilot to streamline workflows, enhance productivity, improve solution quality, and accelerate delivery of business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in data conversion, warehousing, systems analysis, or ETL/ELT-focused roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage multiple, large conversion efforts at once&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced SQL skills - complex queries, joins, performance tuning (SQL Server, ANSI SQL, Python preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer-facing communication skills—you can explain technical issues without hiding behind jargon&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use and understanding of data dictionaries, source to target mapping, and relational database concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High attention to detail and a problem-solving mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to AI for data analysis, validation, or development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Databricks, Snowflake, or similar, a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with ETL tools similar to SSIS, Talend, or Informatica, a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using generative AI tools such as Claude and Copilot to improve productivity and deliver high-quality outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Data Analytics or a related field&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bridgeway is an equal opportunity employer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Systems Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; to join our growing Professional Services organization. As a Systems Analyst, you will work directly with our Business Analysts and customers to review and refine requirements and technical specifications, to create documents, forms and reports from scratch. Additionally, you will integrate the documents you create into the customers’ basys software, to satisfy their business needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a remote position. East coast candidates preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Business Analysts to understand the customer’s request, including data mapping and process flows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and configure customer documents such as Checks and Forms and automate workflow solutions using our proprietary software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Business Analysts on business and technical requirements, to produce clearly defined document and workflow specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with translating requirements into documents, forms, letters, and other correspondences, to produce customer approved deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and revise complex batch, on-demand and interactive document templates, accurately mapping data fields, constructing grouping, repeating rows, headers, logos, pagination, etc., as applicable per the defined requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with software developers to request data source changes and process modifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with customers and other stakeholders on the implementation, configuration, testing, and troubleshooting of our integrated document creation and management tool.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize multiple tools and resources to resolve customer questions and issues in the areas of data, system configuration, setup, and product functionality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage generative AI tools such as Claude and Copilot to streamline workflows, enhance productivity, improve solution quality, and accelerate delivery of business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-2 years of professional experience as a Systems Analyst, including report creation, forms development, mapping fields of data, testing, troubleshooting and technical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid knowledge of data sources and database concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with SSRS, Tableau, Power BI, or similar tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to the use of functions, parameters, XML, XSLT, a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate technical document development requests and issues, in terms understandable to both technical and non-technical audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to handle multiple projects, prioritize tasks, and meet deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using generative AI tools such as Claude and Copilot to improve productivity and deliver high-quality outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelors’ degree in Information Technology, Business Information Systems, or a related discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

